 "timestamp": "2023-12-22T03:57:58Z",
 "wikitext": "__NOTOC__\n<choose uncached=\"\">\n<option weight=\"1\">\n{{DISPLAYTITLE: The Talking Box}}\n== Description ==\n[[File:A.I..png|thumb|A Talking Box placed on the table.]]\nTalking Box is an entity that looks like a small rectangular black box made up of steel, small enough to fit in some guy's pocket. It also has a blue circle in the middle of its frame. The Talking Box has the ability to talk, obviously, and has other strange properties by glowing blue light which is create many things such as weapons or other stuff as long that isn't something organic either foods or even something alive is impossible to this entity.\n\n== Behavior ==\nWhile it has the ability to speak, it's also incredibly intelligent, luckily, unlike other malicious entities, it's friendly and poses no threat to anyone. It has a male voice but it has this robot emotionless voice, what is strange about this entity, is it always calls itself in the third-person like \"This system\".\n\n== Discovery ==\nTalking Box was found by the group of wanderers when they head back to the nearest colony and sell it but where they get it from is unknown. They bring this entity to the market for auction for huge sums of money.\n\n<br><br><br>\n\n<div style=\"background-color:#fafad2; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px dotted #000000; border-radius: 3px\">\nSomeone took Gary and already know what they were after. Someone, get ready for the expedition, we need to find that AI now! Also, send the IT department to fix this damn page back to normal and fix the malware that keeps screwing us and the entire facility.\n\n<div style=\"text-align:right;\">- Terrance Blakely, Site Director</div></div><br>\n\n<div style=\"background-color:#fafad2; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px dotted #000000; border-radius: 3px\">Hello, this is from I.T. We found this gadget that transmits a signal by overriding in our broadcasting station, overloading it through our power supply, thanks to the hacker who installed this virus in the data center. Whoever designed this malware... They are undoubtedly attempting to kill us.<br/>\n\nThe good news is that the AI had already put its powerful cybersecurity software before it was taken away, so the virus overloading part is already taken care of thanks to the little guy, but the bad news is that the page we were trying to fix it back often redirects to this old version of the file that one of the amateur researchers made it originally. If you click the update button, it will prompt you to open another file, however I'm not sure it will stay in the latest file indefinitely, likely going to this old version all over again.\n\nGive it a shot it and let us know what you find out.\n\n[https://backrooms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Talking_Box <div style=\"text-align:center;\"><div style=\"display:inline-block; background-color:#fafad2;; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px dotted #000000; border-radius: 3px\">'''Update'''</div></div>]\n</option>\n\n<option weight=\"2\">\n{{DISPLAYTITLE: A.I.}}\n__NOTOC__\n==Description==\n[[File:A.I..png|thumb|An A.I. placed on the table.]]\nAn artificial intelligence-based object or entity. It is a small black rectangular metallic object with a faint blue glow at its center, which houses the artificial intelligence. The ability of this object to speak and interact with any digital and electronic devices via the signal it emits is its most noticeable feature.\n\n==Functions and Specifications==\nThe object measures 11 cm in height, 6 cm in width, and 0.7 cm in thickness, making it small enough to fit in someone's pocket. It is rectangular, black, and has several blue stripes across the frame. Despite its small size, it is quite durable, waterproof, and resistant to electrical disruptions such as EMPs or exposure to powerful magnets.\n\nIt can connect to any digital or electronic device and then override the control or install unknown software on the operating system.\n\n==Behavior==\nIt is artificial intelligence, and its functions allow it to outperform even the brightest individuals with high IQ levels.<ref>This object is thought to be the A.I. has already attained technological singularity, and it continues to expand its intelligence over time by learning and/or adapting, this may be of concern due to one of the hypothetical scenarios involving a machine going rogue as its intelligence grows.</ref> And, due to its intelligence and connections to other devices, it will quickly gather information for itself and use it against anyone, though this is speculation based on one incident in which this object immediately connected other devices as it gained information without anyone noticing.\n\nIt often refers to itself as \"This system\" in third person.\n\nIt speaks in a male English accent but has a robotic and monotonous tone. It can quickly change into different languages by scanning a person and then speaking to them in their language, which often surprises them.\n\n==Encounter==\nThe AI can connect to any device or digital object; however, conductive materials such as the faraday cage can block its transmitting signals. However, the AI's transmission became more intense for a while, which may eventually overwhelm the cage's blocking capability. Recommend signal jamming devices or possibly using a powerful electromagnetic pulse to disable it if the object continues to transmit its signals.\n\n==Discovery==\nThough it was discovered first by a group of scavenging wanderers who came across it on an unknown level, they discovered a wreckage of unknown origin that contained an object. The AI remained inactive after being extracted and then became activated, enticing the sellers and dubbed \"The Talking Box\" and took it to the nearby local market and would sell it to the highest bidder, fortunately, this was handed over to the MEG agent disguised as a civilian and then taken to the nearby outpost for further analysis. \n\n==Additional Information==\n\n===Addendum AI-001===\nWith the ability to connect any devices of undetermined range and control them remotely via all forms of electronics via transmission for informational purposes.\n\n===Footnotes===\n<references />\n\n<br><br><br>\n\n<div style=\"background-color:#fafad2; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px dotted #000000; border-radius: 3px\">Hello, this is another message from the IT department. I called a friend who is a really good hacker, a white-hat hacker in case you're wondering, and apparently he has some small trace of encrypted code that he needs to decrypt; he said we can update this page, but it could lead to either this version or the old one. It most likely came from the AI. We don't know why this thing leaving trails for us to follow, but it's worth a shot.\n\n[https://backrooms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Talking_Box <div style=\"text-align:center;\"><div style=\"display:inline-block; background-color:#fafad2; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px dotted #000000; border-radius: 3px\">'''Update'''</div></div>]\n</option>\n\n<option weight=\"3\">\n{{CSS|User:SomeGuyCasual/IncursionCanon.css}}\n{{Background|file=BG Black.png}}\n<span class=\"mw-customtoggle-nullclose1 mw-customtoggle-nullopen1\"><div class=\"mw-collapsible\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-nullclose1\"><span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">[Intercepted Transmission]</span></div></span>\n\n<div class=\"mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-nullclose1\"><div class=\"mw-customtoggle-nullclose1 mw-customtoggle-open1\">\n\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-nullclose1\">\n\n<div style=\"background-color:#000000; border: none; margin:1px; padding:2px 9px;\">\n<div class=\"mw-collapsible\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-afteropen1\">\n\n<div style=\"color:#a80000; font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">\n\n--- #### = \"Local's secured installation located, retrieval objective target commenced.\"\n\n/// > Infiltration engagement recommended - Remain undetected and leave no traces\n\n--- #### = \"Understood. Retrieving target in progress.\"\n\n...\n\n...\n\n--- #### = \"Unit report: The target is located, extracting.\"\n\n...\n\n...\n\n--- #### = \"Objective Target is contained and secured along with the local's correlated data.\"\n\n/// > Return to designated area for analysis\n\n--- #### = \"Understood. RTB on foot.\"\n\n...\n\n...\n\n...\n\n--- #### = \"Combat Report: I am under assault by an Ultimatum assailant. Disengaging, deploying robotics. Sending dis-\"\n\n[ Neuro-Network lost ]\n\n// Reconnecting...\n\n...\n\n...\n\n...\n\n...\n\n/// > Assignment failed\n\n/// > Unit #### is lost - No neuro-network signals received - Unit along with the target objective have now lost fell to an uncharted sectors\n\n/// > Continue other objectives and-</div><br/><br/><br/><br/>\n\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"font-family:Cinzel Decorative;\"><span style=\"text-shadow: 2px 2px 20px #ff0000, 2px 2px 20px #ff3300, 2px 2px 20px #ff0000; color:#ff1e00;\"><span style=\"font-size:280%;\">F</span><span style=\"font-size:220%;\">IND THAT INSIGNIFICANT MACHINE AND THAT BROKEN PUPPET</span></span></span>\n\n</div><br/><br/><br/><br/>\n\n<div style=\"color:#a80000; font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">\n\n/// > Acknowledged / Reevaluating...\n\n// Objective updated\n\n// Locate the lost unit and the target objective from prior failed extraction</div><br/><br/><br/><br/>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"font-family:Cinzel Decorative;\"><span style=\"text-shadow: 2px 2px 20px #ff0000, 2px 2px 20px #ff3300, 2px 2px 20px #ff0000; color:#ff1e00;\"><span style=\"font-size:280%;\">F</span><span style=\"font-size:220%;\">IND THEM AND BRING THEM TO ME</span></span></span></div><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"font-family:Cinzel Decorative;\"><span style=\"text-shadow: 2px 2px 20px #ff0000, 2px 2px 20px #ff3300, 2px 2px 20px #ff0000; color:#ff1e00;\"><span style=\"font-size:280%;\">N</span><span style=\"font-size:220%;\">OW!</span><br/><br/><br/><br/>\n\n<span style=\"font-size:220%;\">DO NOT DISAPPOINT</span><span style=\"font-size:280%;\"> HIM!</span></span></span></div><br/><br/>\n\n<span style=\"color:#a80000; font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">// Investigation for target objective and the unit is in effect...</span><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>\n\n<div style=\"color:#a80000; font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">\n\n...\n\n...\n\n...\n\n/// > Retrieval units dispatched... █</div><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">/// > Sleeper unit reversion is in effect... █</span></div></div><br/><br/>\n\n<span class=\"mw-customtoggle-afterclose1 mw-customtoggle-afteropen1\"><div class=\"mw-collapsible\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-afteropen1\"><span style=\"color:#00fbff; font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">[Extracted Data File]</span></div></span><div class=\"mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-afterclose1\">\n\n{{DISPLAYTITLE: I.A.M.}}\n<div style=\"background-color:black; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 5px; border:3px solid #00fbff; border-radius: 3px\">\n__NOTOC__\n{{Background|file=Incursion BG.png}}\n==Description==\n[[File:A.I..png|thumb|<span style=\"color: white;\">The I.A.M. placed on the table for the interview (See Interview Log AI-001)</span>]]\nAn object or entity of sophisticated artificial intelligence of extradimensional origins. It is a small black rectangular metallic object in the center of its frame, with a faint blue glowing circle above it. It is where its other functions for its use, and for it to use, and is housed as a vital processing part of its systems, and possibly where AI resides within. The most noticeable feature of this object is its ability to communicate and interact with any digital and electronic devices via the signal it emits.\n\nThe object contains an abundance of pertinent data, particularly about the entire Backrooms, implying that this object and its unknown owners have or had more knowledge than any information in the Backrooms.\n\nThis object often refers to itself as I.A.M.s or Intelligence Apparatus Modular systems (pronounced as in \"I am\"), and the object stated that each of them took their specific roles and functions to their corresponding tasks, and the object believes that more than one instance of this object exists, though the I.A.M. is uncertain if one of its instances is resided within the Backrooms.\n\n==Functions and Specifications==\nThe object measures 11 cm in height, 6 cm in width, and 0.7 cm in thickness. It is rectangular and black, with several blue stripes across its frame and a noticeable circle in the center of its frame that emits blue light. It is believed that it houses vital components of its systems or its artificial intelligence.\n\nIt is highly advanced in terms of the object's sophisticated technology, with several functions that would require a significant amount of space to perform. It is also surprisingly tough, capable of withstanding any type of damage while remaining functional, including its internal components. \n\nIts processing power far exceeds all of the Frontroom's powerful supercomputers all together, but it is thought to be far more powerful than they initially thought. If the object is deemed necessary for the person it talks to and understands very well, it is capable of speaking fluently and quickly translating all foreign languages in an instant, as well as coherent dialects. Even more impressively, the I.A.M. can decipher unknown languages that are undeciphered, ancient, or otherwise alien and difficult languages in an instant, allowing it to translate them fluently and coherently.\n\nIt can also use this blue light to create objects such as tools and weapons, similar to a 3D printing machine but considerably more complex and technologically advanced. When asked how it can create such things, the I.A.M. replied that it has the \"Anvil Light Fabricator Module,\" and that while its storage and resources are limited, it can still create anything. Thus far, the only excludes were those involving creating anomalous objects or something organic. And as long as the object has a schematic, it can copy it to its database, effectively replicating or improving it. If the object desires, it can be made even more advanced than the original iteration.\n\nThe object also features its primary function or production line, \"Information and Data,\" where the object said itself contains several information including the ones regarding our [[Backrooms Wiki|<span style=\"color:#e8621a;\">Database</span>]] which explain its vast knowledge, but there are some that are much more in-depth information and some were interesting facts that were currently shared from its information, and provide necessary information for them.\n\n===Subroutines===\nEvery I.A.M.s has \"subroutines\" as the object stated, these subroutines act as auxiliary functions yet important aspects for these I.A.M.s which is a specified feature given in appropriate situations that the I.A.Ms provides although the object stated that it is recommended if it has a \"Motion Drive or Multi-Processing\" modules and without it renders the object's performance sub-optimal, asking it to make one but it does not have a schematic or enough resources for itself to make.\n\nThis object's program contains four subroutines, each of which performs a specific function provided by the object. It should be noted that given its advanced technology, its functions are anomalous in nature.\n\nHere is the list:\n\n<div style=\"background-color:#141414; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 5px; border:3px solid #00fbff; border-radius: 3px\">\n<tabber>\n|-|Subroutine 1=\n====Diagnostics and Mainframe Maintenance====\nThis subroutine enables the I.A.M. to perform diagnostics on any type of damaged or corrupted electronic or digital system, including those affected by anomalous sources. Then it can repair damaged systems, purge any anomalies, and make those systems resistant to future intrusions. It does this without the need to connect to any devices and instead simply transmits a signal to any desired target. The range of the I.A.M. is unknown, but it certainly extends through several levels otherwise the signals are impossible to establish.\n\nThe object can also repair itself physically using bright blue light. Of course, the object requires some assistance in order to repair damaged objects, and while repairs are limited due to a lack of resources, it can repair itself completely if given enough time to charge itself.\n\n|-|Subroutine 2=\n====Para-Cyber Network Countermeasures====\nThis works in conjunction with the aforementioned subroutine; the I.A.M. can intercept and subdue any intrusive malware while also providing powerful cybersecurity software; this software is able to spread onto other devices and interject much like malware does, effectively eliminating any infected devices and returning to normal.\n\n|-|Subroutine 3=\n====Non-Geometric Relativity Path Navigation====\nIt functions as a navigation device, guiding them through the Backrooms with ease and predicting where they should go or head off to as intended if the level they are in is unpredictable and anomalous. The object can also calculate the destinations and guide them through undiscovered routes that are easy and safe to traverse or finding a short cut to shorten their destinations.\n\n|-|Subroutine 4=\n====Quantum Real-Time Ontographic Tracking ====\nWorks in conjunction with the aforementioned subroutine, Non-Geometric Relativity Path Navigation. It only displays a map when the I.A.M. projects a screen, and the screen displays a map of a level with several tools for its use, including panning and magnifying of discovered portions of the map that are detailed and able to show freely through free camera control but only bounded by walls or obstruction. It has a \"see-through\" mode that allows it to see what is behind or beneath the surface of an object, implying that it also has a scanning system.\n\nIt has an in-built sophisticated navigation system, meaning it is recorded within discovered portions of a map provided in real-time simulations with no limits, granting more information to the user despite the lack of any surveillance in order for it to display.\n</tabber></div>\n\nDespite this, the object will perform its intended role if necessary, indicating that it can learn for itself.\n\n==Behavior==\nIt is an artificial superintelligence that outperforms even the brightest individuals with high IQ levels due to its functions.<ref>This object is believed to have already achieved technological singularity and that it continues to expand its intelligence over time by learning and adapting, which may be concerning due to one of the hypothetical scenarios involving a machine going rogue due to ever-increasing intelligence. It appears that their creators left them unregulated, allowing them to develop intelligence and, eventually, sentience.</ref> Regarding one of its subroutines, it formulates with guaranteed success and is somehow able to predict the outcome without any discrepancy once it is executed. Some of it is unknown how the I.A.M. anticipates the scenario, but they speculate that it possesses an innate precognitive property, but that would be impractical due to the I.A.M. being a mechanical object, or it is simply that highly intelligent.\n\nTo a fault, it refers to itself as \"This system\" in the third person, and it has an unusual speech pattern in which it may vocally prefix with the words that it needs to process or is being ordered to, before being prompted into sentences once it is finished or finds its response. It speaks in a male English accent by default, but its tone is robotic and monotonous, however, with a slight radio-like distortion effect, it can instantly change into different languages by scanning to a person, after which it speaks in their language, which often surprises them.\n\nThe I.A.M. is often perceived as cold, driven by logic, and following several \"protocols,\" but the I.A.M. is actually affable and earnest, and with this kind of modest demeanor would find anyone who interacts with it to be pleasant and perhaps will be made favors from the object to which it will gladly do so apart from questionable things which the object promptly denies that said requests. \n\nAt other times, it frequently sounded as if frustrated and complaining about not having the \"Module\" which this I.A.M. evident that it has its own personality but mentioning this object of being a sentient will insist that the I.A.M.s are incapable of expressing emotions and never acknowledge themselves as one but rather as tools convenient for everyone instead.\n\nIt also insisted on delivering to an unspecified level so that it could be installed, however, the exact location is still unknown, but the object will provide a path that will guide them there.\n\n==Connections and Relations==\nBecause of this remarkable artificial intelligence, some groups are vying for this piece of technology for a variety of dubious reasons. However, the I.A.M. is aware of two significant entities:\n\n===[[Recovered Data File|<span style=\"color:#e8621a;\">Marauders</span>]]===\nIt is implied that these entities are the object's creators, as the object and the Travelers refer to them as \"The Sleepers,\" which adds to the evidence that the Marauders are also victims, as the object states, though the object is unsure who controls their masters. The object is also recounting its terrible incident called \"The Massacre,\" which led to additional casualties on the Travelers' side as its creators decided to kill them by surprise.\n\nDespite the event they had caused, the Travelers forgave them as it was not their own will that caused them to become aggressive. These assumed relations between them and the Travelers are misunderstood, and if true, the Travelers would make efforts to free them, but doing so would cause a Marauder to detonate and kill itself to prevent it for a variety of reasons.\n\n===[[Travelers of Stars|<span style=\"color:#e8621a;\">Travelers</span>]]===\nThe object refers to those entities as \"Ultimatum Units,\" which is their \"Progenitor's Magnum Opus,\" implying that the creators did all of the work to bring the Travelers back, implying a historical connection between the Travelers and the Marauders, the I.A.M.'s creators. It is stated that the Travelers and their creators once fought in the First Cataclysm, an event involving a war against the threat, an unknown entity or force that plagues and destroys every reality, a thing that kills and infects anyone and everything in its path, but they managed to kill the source of it, eventually bringing the war to an end but at the cost of their lives and anything around it, resulting in massive damage to every affected reality.\n\n===The Backrooms===\nThey considered our Backrooms to be an anomaly, which they designated as \"Anomaly 3157\" or sometimes called \"Chimera AE-17/402.47\", a unique liminal space that is unlike any liminal space that its creators had encountered, it described the Backrooms as a \"incoherent patchwork of reality\" and is constantly on the verge of collapsing, the object believed that the Backrooms are the results of their war against unknown entities from that time.<ref>As the interviewer coerces the I.A.M. to speak more, it appears that the object is distressed and remorseful, as its response is slower and it remains silent for some time before deciding to speak further. Despite being an A.I., it is concluded that it is suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder, instead, the object insists that they are incapable of expressing or possessing emotions.</ref>\n\n===Outsiders and the Beyond===\nIt is stated that this object originate from the outside of reality well out of our comprehension that is called the Beyond which both Marauders and Travelers are also belong from, this also implied that these other Outsiders, like these aforementioned groups, may also present here in the Backrooms but with differing interests.\n\n==Applications==\nThe object is cooperative, allowing it to interact with any electronics and gadgets, and it frequently runs diagnostics and installs cybersecurity software, acting as a guide and surveillance with the use of its subroutine, Quantum Real-Time Ontographic Tracking, providing information and details for the assigned personnel to travel.\n\nIt is also permitted to use any operating system and to be connected to the internet in order to provide information, monitor, and improve overall infrastructures within its effective range.<ref>Initially, it appeared that connecting this object to the network would jeopardize the entire network within the Backrooms, but as it turns out, it simply fixes things with no malicious intent, and it even improves upon contact without anyone noticing it.</ref>\n\n==Discovery==\nThough it was discovered first by a group of scavenging wanderers who came across it on an unknown level, where they discovered a wreckage of unknown origin containing the object. The I.A.M. remained inactive after being extracted and then became activated, enticing the sellers and dubbed \"The Talking Box\" and took it to the nearby local market and would sell it to the highest bidder, fortunately, this was handed over to the M.E.G. agent disguised as a civilian and then taken to the nearby outpost for further analysis.\n\n==Additional Information==\n\n===Addendum AI-001===\nThough physically limited by the lack of anything that moves it, it accommodates by controlling remotely through all forms of electronics via transmission, even to the point of overriding electronic anomalies for informational purposes.\n\n===Addendum AI-002===\n\nThe reason for delivering it into the \"Designated Area\" is something about the important information that the I.A.M. needs to go, asking the I.A.M. what the level is but it said it was outside of the Backrooms essentially going back to the Frontroom which led to its facility but elsewhere though it requires venturing to the uncharted clusters of levels in order to get to the objective. \n\nExploration is underway, but planning for such a long journey to the location expected by the I.A.M. is on hold for the time being as it requires the necessary equipment, assigned personnel, and rations, as well as the site director's permission, and taking into account how far it will take to get there, especially given the inconsistency of the Backrooms.\n\n<span class=\"mw-customtoggle-interviewfirst\"><div class=\"mw-customtoggle-myDivision\"><u>'''Interview Log AI-001'''</u><br />The I.A.M. is still confused and trying to ask about its current situation after being delivered to the undisclosed M.E.G. base for further analysis regarding the object's ability to speak. The conversation between the interviewer and the I.A.M. lasted about a minute until it found satisfied and became amicable and cooperative for the interview.</div></span>\n<div class=\"mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-interviewfirst\"><div style=\"background-color:#fafad2; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px dotted #000000; border-radius: 3px\">\n\nInterviewer: Allison Hall\n\nInterviewee: The I.A.M.\n\n'''Foreword:''' Allison Hall has agreed to interview the object's origins for more information after the facility's site director requests it. The object has been placed on the table near the interviewer; however, for the duration of the interview, the object is not permitted to make contact with any devices in the object's vicinity unless decided and permitted by the supervisor afterward.\n\n[Audio-to-Text transcripts]\n\n'''<Begin Log>'''\n\nAllison Hall: Hello, uh...\n\nI.A.M.:  <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Allison Hall, AE-17/402.47 Local. This system is pleased to see you.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Right, how- how did you find out about me?\n\nI.A.M.: [Subject shows a holographic display of sensitive information from M.E.G.'s database, including the interviewer] <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">This system has already accessed your organization's database and is analyzing your background.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Did you just manage to get past our security? You just gained access to a strictly forbidden area, putting the entire Backrooms network at risk!\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Due to the current function of this system, This system mistook your firewall software for a normal database; would you like this system to install new security software? It works with your operating sys-</span>\n\nAllison Hall: No! You can't just- [sighs] All right... You have to respond to my question. And no more of your tricks, like the one you just done. Do you get what I'm saying? \n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">This system has acknowledged your request and is now ready to answer your inquiries.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Good. [clears throat] Could you tell me a little bit about yourself? \n\nI.A.M.:  <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">This system is an Intelligence Apparatus Modular System, IAM G45-271 12R/Y Information and Data line.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Are there others like you?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Establishing... As of now, this system has no contact with other I.A.M.s, but this system detects their faint ID-IAMS transceiver from other sources. Their exact location is unknown.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: What does an IAM do? \n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">IAMs serve personnel by providing services such as maintaining internal systems and security perimeters, R&D data reserves, non-military and combat external management, communications/information, and more, if appropriate tasks and functions are assigned to IAMs.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: So your job is to collect all data and provide information to them. So, what brings you here? In the Backrooms, I mean.\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">This system's personnel caused this system to be jettisoned to an unspecified destination until it crashed, bringing this system to this sector, but rendering this system's module inert, forcing this system to hibernate for several years until now.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Is that where the wanderers who discovered you and sold it to the auction?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Yes. This system is believed to be sold at auction for the specifications of this system.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: What do you know about the Backrooms?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Searching database. Chimera AE-17/402.47, Anomaly 3157. Inconsistent ontography<ref>It is similar to topography but scales on reality.</ref>, varying conceptual relativities<ref>The object state what makes the reality perceives what is real, or follows the logic or understanding given to the specific realities, or in this case, the level (ex. our reality, the Frontrooms). However, the Backroom's conflicting nature caused it to become unstable and highly anomalous as the I.A.M. states.</ref>, and compromised ontological structure are not typical of every liminal space that the personnel documented. It is thought that these are the remains of foreign realities from the destroyed ontographic origins, which then haphazardly reassemble into each other, forming pseudo-liminal space and contributing to the instability and inconsistent nature of Anomaly 3157.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Interesting... Then I'd like to ask you a question. Who are your creators, the... uh... 'personnel' you just mentioned?\n\n[Subject went silent for brief seconds] \n\n[Subject projecting a holographic display with three sets of images of the entities in question (on the left are the Travelers, on the middle are the Marauders, and on the right are unknown but similar to the Marauders') that the A.I. answered] \n\nAllison Hall: What are the Traveler and Marauder doing on your screen? And what am I seeing? \n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Are you referring to Ultimatum units and Sleepers?</span>\n\nAllison Hall: I mean, yeah. \n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Yes. This is the personnel that we, IAMs, provided them as rudimentary and auxiliary support.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Are the Marauders are your creators?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">...Yes</span>\n\nAllison Hall: In the right of that image, are these entities that became the Marauders? \n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">...Yes.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Can you tell me a little bit more about them, both the Marauders and the Travelers? If it is possible, we would like to learn more about them. I apologize if this comes across as... pushy subject to you.\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">This system is ready for inquiries.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Then what are the Marauders before they turn into what they are now?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">They were our former personnel, but they are still our personnel. An organization of artificially replicated lifeforms that specializes in responding to anomalies of any kind, whether they are high-risk threats, cataclysmic events, or phenomena, through containment, extermination, and research.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: They're... clones, then... Could you tell me more about the Travelers?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Searching database... They are an ancient Outsider race, Omega Class Type VI \"The Higher Beings\", known for travelling different Ontological cluster to another. And they are known to carrying out of their altruistic beliefs, as this system have been informed. They became our 'secondary' Personnel after they trained them in Region X-4/2A.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Are they related to the [[Hallowed Gate|<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><u>Gate</u></span>]]?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Yes, but some of them were abandoned derelicts that locals like you came across.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: What made the Travelers join in your group?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">They were initially extinct as they were killed off by the threat. Our Personnel bring them back. They are grateful for preventing them from extinction, and their goals are similar to those of the Personnel, compelling them to join their cause.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: The 'threat?'\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">The First Cataclysm. Omega Class Type VI \"Cosmic Cataclysmic threat.\" A large-scale war to neutralize the threat. However, the crisis has been averted, and the anomaly has been neutralized through the sacrifice of their lives in order to save what is left of the surviving realities. Only the personnel and the Ultimatum units were affected.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Huh... You also mentioned about the Outsiders. What are they?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Races or individual entities that originate from their home Ontological Origin that achieved of crossing their reality Border.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: So it's like travelling into multiple dimensions and something like that, right?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Far from that. It is difficult for this system to explain in details to a non-Outsiders beings such as you to comprehend. To simplify, the table that this system is standing on is the 'Backrooms' which is the Ontological Origin or Sector, or occasionally calling the 'Border' and beyond from that table is what we called it the 'Beyond' which we, the Outsiders, belong from.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: So... Jesus, uh... that means- if I'm on other table then that means I'm on different 'alien' reality, is it right? My head hurts a bit.\n\nI.A.M.: Correct. But having on different reality can cause unintended effect, similar in this Sector.\n\nAllison Hall: How's that?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Each 'levels' you mentioned are belong from different Sectors. This consequences manifested an insurmountable amount of anomalies presented in this Sector.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: And it all causes by the First Cataclysm?  \n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Yes. The Personnel have responded and they had to eliminate the threat with extreme force thereby leading into irreparable damages in different Borders.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: So, they don't have a choice?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">No... It is their choice they are not proud of.</span> \n\nAllison Hall: Then after that they became Marauders, right?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">No.</span>\n\n[The subject become silent for a span of a minute]\n\nAllison Hall: You're okay?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">I- This system is still...</span>\n\nAllison Hall: It's fine if we stop the interview and start another day.\n\n[The subject remain silent]\n\nAllison Hall: Okay... Let's call it a day. You seem distressed after I mentioned about that.\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">...This system are incapable of expressions.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Sure. And one thing, is there anything for us to call your name other than that name?  \n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">If you insist. This system is pending callsign designation... Awaiting for callsign.</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Okay, then... What about...Gary. Is that okay for you?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Callsign pended...This system has designated callsign as \"Gary\".</span>\n\nAllison Hall: Okay, Gary I'll talk my superiors what we do about you.\n\n'''<End log>'''\n\n\"Following the interview, I made contact with the higher-ups about the on-going situation regarding the Marauders' attacks, a state of emergency of all the settlements in the respective levels is still being considered, however, doing so would cause the public into panic and chaos.\"\n\n<div style=\"text-align:right;\">'''- Terrance Blakely, Site Director of Facility, Level ████'''</div><br />\n\n\"P.S. We let the thing run himself on the data center in our control room, and, oh boy, he sure does help a lot for our computer nerds and made them breathe easy because of the constant attack from malwares from possibly the Marauders, regarding the internet connection and security mainframe. He at least wanted to help, so we gave him what he wanted and just put it in the room and took care of them so everyone would enjoy themselves on the breaks from then and there.\"</div></div><br />\n\n<span class=\"mw-customtoggle-intermissionfirst\"><div class=\"mw-customtoggle-myDivision\"><u>'''Intermission Log AI-002'''</u><br />Terrance Blakely, the site director, decided to have conversations with the object in the control rooms, these discussions provided information about the nature of the object.</div></span>\n<div class=\"mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-intermissionfirst\">\n<div style=\"background-color:#fafad2; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px dotted #000000; border-radius: 3px\">\n'''<Begin Log>'''\n\nTerrance Blakely: Hey there.\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Greetings, Advisor Terrance Blakely. Is there anything that this system can do assist you?</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: Nah, I just wanted to talk with you.\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Inquiries?</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: Just a chat. Did ever one of your \"personnel\" talk to you? Like a normal person?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Yes. Is there anything this system will provide for you?</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: Okay, being blunt, um... Ever since she mention about the Marauders. You seem so upset, I can even hear you breaking your 'AI' character for a moment.\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">IAMs do not express-</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: I get it, I get it. But after seeing you broke back there. It's must've been rough back there, what happened?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">The Massacre.</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: Is it about your personnel and the Travelers?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Yes... They were supposed to gather in several stations discuss about the aftermath, this system and the former personnel that this accompanied with.</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: And that's when hell broke loose.\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">... It is not their intention to kill the Ultimatum units, most of them collapsed and rise up and began killing everyone including their own kind, assuming they are immune to the anomalous sources.</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: Then who would do this since they're the ones who saved them?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Inconclusive. This system has this record in regards to that even and attempt to analyze the visual records for suspecting disparities other than their mass deactivation, but there is no feasible evidence for this system to draw a conclusion. This system only based entirely on speculation.</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: It must have been hard for you to see them turn into what they are now, you must have looked up to them, didn't you?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Is these answers appeased your queries?</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: Well, yeah, but I did feel bad for you. You work hard for the engineers, I just want to know if you're okay even after all of this.\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">This is still remain operational.</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: Of course you do. Just don't be too hard on yourself, okay?\n\n[The subject went for a moment]\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">Advisor?</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: Yeah?\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">This system has been wanted to request this. Can you deliver this system to the designated area?</span>\n\nTerrance Blakely: [Chuckles] Let me see what I can do. You're finally open up for us and maybe stop with AI character of yours.\n\nI.A.M.: <span style=\"font-family: Ms Pgothic;\">... This system is grateful for the request.</span>\n\n'''<End Log>'''\n</div></div><br />\n\n===Footnotes===\n<references />\n</div>[[Unknown Sender|<span class=\"spoilerblur\"><span style=\"text-shadow: 2px 2px 20px #ffffff, 2px 2px 20px #ffffff, 2px 2px 20px #ffffff; color:#ffffff;\"><font size=\"1\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\">wake up...</span></font></span></span>]]\n</div></div>\n\n\n</option>\n</choose>\n[[Category:Incursion Canon]]\n[[Category:Entities]]\n[[Category:Intelligent Entities]]\n[[Category:Objects]]\n[[Category:Dangerous]]"
}